Shelton is into his seventh ATP Tour final and fifth at ATP 500 level after winning titles in Tokyo in 2023 and Dallas in February, when he saved three championship points to defeat countryman Taylor Fritz. With his semi-final win in Munich, Shelton ensured he will remain as the American No. 1 on Monday.

As well as becoming just the fourth man born in the 2000s to reach five ATP 500 title matches, Shelton is the first American to reach back-to-back finals on European clay since Jim Courier at Roland Garros in 1991-93.

